FBIS3-7597 "dreas061_a_94019" FBIS-EAS-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Okinawa Assembly Appoints Vice Governor OW3003062594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0608 GMT 30 Mar 94 OW3003062594 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Naha, March 30 KYODO -- The Okinawa Prefectural Assembly on Wednesday [30 March] approved the appointment of Mitsuko Tomon to be vice governor of Japan's southernmost prefecture. Tomon, 51, succeeds Hiroko Sho, 61, also a woman. She is the fourth female vice governor in Japan, officials said.
